```zig PlasmaPlanetV6/src/input.zig:11-14
// Excerpt from: fn updateSelectedCell
    if (rl.isKeyPressed(.up) || rl.isKeyPressedRepeat(.up)) {
        _ = game;
    }

```
src/input.zig:11:25: error: expected error set type, found 'bool'
    if ((rl.isKeyPressed(.up) || rl.isKeyPressedRepeat(.up)) == true) {
         ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~^~~~~
src/input.zig:11:31: note: '||' merges error sets; 'or' performs boolean OR
    if ((rl.isKeyPressed(.up) || rl.isKeyPressedRepeat(.up)) == true) {
The error you're encountering is due to the misuse of the `||` operator, which in Zig is used to merge error sets, not for boolean OR operations. Instead, you should use the `or` operator for boolean OR operations.

Here's the corrected code:

```zig
fn updateSelectedCell(game: *Game) void {
    if (rl.isKeyPressed(.up) or rl.isKeyPressedRepeat(.up)) {
        _ = game;
    }
}
```

In this corrected version, `or` is used to perform the boolean OR operation between `rl.isKeyPressed(.up)` and `rl.isKeyPressedRepeat(.up)`. This should resolve the error you encountered.
